      "description": "Two-loop massless planar double-box (ladder) topology contributing to the electroweak form factor for f fbar -> X with on-shell massless fermions p1^2=p2^2=0 and q=p1+p2. All six propagators massless (denominators D_1, D_2, D_4, D_5, D_7, D_8 in the paper's appendix A1). Computed in full through O(eps^0) in terms of one-dimensional harmonic polylogarithms H(w;x) of x=-s/m^2 (the variable is shared with the massive sibling family for direct comparison). Leading IR pole eps^{-4} (double soft-collinear singularity per loop). The diagram is reducible by IBP but listed as a complete result; cross-checks against Gonsalves (1983) and Van Neerven (1986). Computation chain: tensor reduction with FORM and Mathematica, IBP via SOLVE, differential equations in x integrated in the HPL basis.",
